This paper focuses on structured pruning of convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves using generative adversarial learning (GAN) to optimize the pruning process, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and regularization techniques, which are also common in data science (cs.DS).
